The paper discusses natural user interfaces (NUIs) in mobile computing, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction (HCI) and falls under the cs.HC category. The paper also mentions the use of bio-signal acquisition techniques, which can be related to robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of augmented, mixed, and virtual reality (AR/MR/VR), which can be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and AR/MR/VR (cs.AR).
